The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Mahindras post 41% rise in earnings

 July 26 (PTI): Mahindra amp; Mahindra Ltd has posted a 40.55 per cent rise in profit after tax at Rs 204.17 crore for the quarter ended June 30 compared with Rs 145.26 crore for the same period in 2005-06.

 Total income increased 24.53 per cent at Rs 2,281.69 crore against Rs 1,832.22 crore in the corresponding previous quarter, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 The scrip closed at Rs 568.90 on Dalal Street today.

 HPCL loss deepens

 Hindustan Petroleum Corp today reported a higher loss of Rs 607.67 crore for the April-June quarter compared with a net loss of Rs 507.89 crore in the same period last year. 

 The company suffered the loss as it was not able to raise fuel prices in line with the rise in the cost of production.

 Even after the June 5 price rise, we are losing Rs 5.59 a litre on petrol, Rs 7.84 per litre on diesel, Rs 133 per LPG cylinder and Rs 18 a litre on kerosene, HPCL chairman and managing director M.B. Lal said.

 Colgate Palmolive

 Colgate Palmolive India Ltd has reported a 28.87 per cent rise in profit after tax at Rs 36.06 crore for the quarter ended June 30 against Rs 27.98 crore in the corresponding previous quarter.

 Total income increased 19.13 per cent at Rs 324.35 crore compared with Rs 272.26 crore in the year-ago period.

 The scrip closed at Rs 394.30, up 4.52 per cent, on the BSE today.

 Sun Pharmaceutical

 Sun Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd has recorded a 19.84 per cent rise in profit after tax at Rs 148.02 crore for the quarter ended June 30 compared with Rs 123.51 crore a year ago. Total income surged 26.84 per cent to Rs 565.96 crore from Rs 446.18 crore last year. 




